
@startuml
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam noteStyle box

class Student {
  +String studentID
  +String name
  +List<Course> coursesRegistered
  +requestAppointment(course: Course, date: Date, time: Time)
}

class TeachingAssistant {
  +String taID
  +String name
  +List<Course> coursesTaught
  +acceptAppointment(appointment: Appointment)
  +rejectAppointment(appointment: Appointment)
}

class Course {
  +String courseCode
  +String courseName
  +List<Student> studentsRegistered
  +List<TeachingAssistant> teachingAssistants
}

class Appointment {
  +String appointmentID
  +Date date
  +Time time
  +Course course
  +TeachingAssistant ta
  +Student student
  +boolean status // e.g., pending, accepted, rejected
}

Student "1" -- "many" Course : registeredFor
Course "1" -- "1" TeachingAssistant : hasTA
Course "1" -- "many" Appointment : hasAppointments
TeachingAssistant "1" -- "many" Appointment : handles
Student "1" -- "1" Appointment : requests
Appointment "1" -- "1" Course : forCourse
Appointment "1" -- "1" TeachingAssistant : withTA
Appointment "1" -- "1" Student : byStudent

@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:
- **Student** can request an **Appointment** only if they are registered for a **Course**.
- A **Course** has one or more **Teaching Assistants** who can handle appointments.
- An **Appointment** is associated with exactly one **Course**, one **Teaching Assistant**, and one **Student**.
- The **Appointment** has a status (e.g., pending, accepted, rejected) to manage the flow of requests.

